A frontline Non Governmental Organization (NGO), ASATTAHIR Foundation has felicitated with women the world over, especially Nigerian women as they mark Women’s Day on Sunday March 8, 2020. This was contained in a statement signed by its founder, Malam Aliyu Sidi Attahiru made available to newsmen on Sunday, which described women as the mothers of the nation. “Women are the pillars of the world. Their importance to all spheres of life cannot be overemphasized. “Besides child bearing, they nurture and groom the children, with some of recent, becoming bread winners of their families,” it stated. ASATTAHIR Foundation charged men to treat women with respect and shun all forms of domestic violence. “Such acts like rape, assault and harassment of women should become a thing of the past. “Women are gifts from God and should be treated as such,” it added.